STREPTOCOCCUS, GROUP A, SCARLET FEVER - UK (08): (ENGLAND)
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 22 Aug 2016
Source: Lincolnshire Echo [edited]
http://www.lincolnshireecho.co.uk/new-scarlet-fever-cases-confirmed-in-lincolnshire/story-29642717-detail/story.html


Public Health England has confirmed that there were 4 new cases of scarlet fever in Lincolnshire in its latest report.

For the week ending [14 Aug 2016], there were 3 cases in Lincoln and 1 case in West Lindsey.

Nationally, the figures show there were 132 new cases of the bacterial illness -- which mainly affects children.

[Byline: Caroline Wilson]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As of 30 Apr 2016, a total of 12 906 scarlet fever notifications had been made, with notifications peaking at the end of March [2016] in England since the season began in September 2015; and the areas with the highest population rates to date are Devon, Cornwall & Somerset (3.9 per 100 000 population), Yorkshire & Humber (3.7/100 000), and the North East (http://tinyurl.com/jtm44vu). Lincolnshire, for which data are given in the news report above, is partly in the Yorkshire & Humber region and partly in the East Midlands region of England. A map of the regions of England can be found at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regions_of_England.

For the same period in 2014-2015, there were 9379 cases (https://www.gov.uk/government/news/update-on-rising-scarlet-fever-across-england). 2015-2016 is the 3rd season in a row in which elevated scarlet fever activity has been noted. A total of 15 637 notifications were made in England and Wales in 2014, rising to 17 590 in 2015 (https://www.gov.uk/government/news/update-on-rising-scarlet-fever-across-england).

Maps of England can be seen at http://www.picturesofengland.com/images/mapofengland/england-counties.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4437081,2210.
Lincolnshire is an historical county on the east coast of England (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lincolnshire). Maps of England can be seen at http://www.picturesofengland.com/images/mapofengland/england-counties.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4437081,279. - Mod.ML]
